From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Sun, 1 Feb 2026 19:36:00 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] net: realtek: fix shutdown panic in r8125/r8126 get_stats64

During system poweroff, netif_carrier_off() in the shutdown path
schedules a linkwatch_event on the events_unbound workqueue.  This
event fires asynchronously after the PCIe device has already been
powered down, calling get_stats64 -> dump_tally_counter which does
MMIO to the dead device.  On ARM64 this triggers a fatal SError.

Check R8125_FLAG_DOWN / R8126_FLAG_DOWN before the MMIO tally dump.
The flag is already set in close() before netif_carrier_off(), so
the ordering is correct.  Cached counter values are still returned.
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/realtek/r8125/r8125_n.c | 6 ++++--
 drivers/net/ethernet/realtek/r8126/r8126_n.c | 6 ++++--
 2 files changed, 8 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/realtek/r8125/r8125_n.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/realtek/r8125/r8125_n.c
index 3d775975bfc42..783c7b4c712c8 100755
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/realtek/r8125/r8125_n.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/realtek/r8125/r8125_n.c
@@ -17026,9 +17026,11 @@ rtl8125_get_stats64(struct net_device *dev, struct rtnl_link_stats64 *stats)
 
         /*
          * Fetch additional counter values missing in stats collected by driver
-         * from tally counters.
+         * from tally counters.  Skip if device is shutting down to avoid MMIO
+         * to a powered-down PCIe endpoint (causes ARM SError on shutdown).
          */
-        rtl8125_dump_tally_counter(tp, paddr);
+        if (!test_bit(R8125_FLAG_DOWN, tp->task_flags))
+                rtl8125_dump_tally_counter(tp, paddr);
 
         stats->tx_errors = le64_to_cpu(counters->tx_errors);
         stats->collisions = le32_to_cpu(counters->tx_multi_collision);
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/realtek/r8126/r8126_n.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/realtek/r8126/r8126_n.c
index 0ca695efe7efd..9174cee339773 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/realtek/r8126/r8126_n.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/realtek/r8126/r8126_n.c
@@ -13367,9 +13367,11 @@ rtl8126_get_stats64(struct net_device *dev, struct rtnl_link_stats64 *stats)
 
         /*
          * Fetch additional counter values missing in stats collected by driver
-         * from tally counters.
+         * from tally counters.  Skip if device is shutting down to avoid MMIO
+         * to a powered-down PCIe endpoint (causes ARM SError on shutdown).
          */
-        rtl8126_dump_tally_counter(tp, paddr);
+        if (!test_bit(R8126_FLAG_DOWN, tp->task_flags))
+                rtl8126_dump_tally_counter(tp, paddr);
 
         stats->tx_errors = le64_to_cpu(counters->tx_errors);
         stats->collisions = le32_to_cpu(counters->tx_multi_collision);
